The Herald Kudakwashe Mugari, Maputo, Mozambique PRESIDENT Mnangagwa who left Harare this morning has arrived in Maputo, Mozambique for a day long indaba as SADC moves in to counter insurgency in that country. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-520305" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/HE-in-Moza-5.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/HE-in-Moza-5.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/HE-in-Moza-5-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The President was welcomed at the Maputo International Airport by Zimbabwe’s Ambassador to Mozambique Retired Lieutenant General Douglas Nyikayaramba, embassy staff and Mozambique government officials. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-520314" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/HE-in-Moza-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/HE-in-Moza-2.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/HE-in-Moza-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> As the then chairperson of the SADC Organ on Defence and Security, President Mnangagwa oversaw the moulding of a regional response against Islamists Insurgency in the northern region of Mozambique. The President is here along with his counterparts Botswana President Mokwetse Masisis(Troika chair) Cyrill Ramaphosa of South Africa (incoming troika chair) and President Phillip Nyusi who is the host. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-520315" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/HE-in-Moza.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/HE-in-Moza.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/HE-in-Moza-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The meeting will be chaired by President Masisi. Today’s meeting is a continuation to last month Gaborone SADC extraordinary meeting where leaders discussed steps to help end the insurgency in the Mozambican province of Cabo Del gado Province, where more than 3000 people have been killed and thousands left homeless. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-520316" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-14-at-11.15.41.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-14-at-11.15.41.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/12/WhatsApp-Image-2020-12-14-at-11.15.41-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />   The Gaborone meeting resolved to help Mozambique end the infighting as this has a major bearing on the Sadc bloc. Sadc countries particulary Zimbabwe use Beira, Maputo and Nakala ports for export and import businesses.